item.description:
Task source: https://github.com/Tzion0/CTF/tree/master/KnightCTF By importing the ELF executable into Ghidra, we quickly noticed that the code will encode our input, store into a variable (We will call it temp by now) and looping through each character of temp to do final comparison with the encoded flag.
The encoding algorithm:
 for (c = 0; inpt[c] != '\0'; c = c + 1) { temp[c] = inpt[c] + -10; if (temp[c] == 'A') { temp[c] = '*'; } } Now, let&rsquo;s see what&rsquo;s the encoded flag:
